cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.SI 

The paper proposes a framework for multi-task learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). The approach involves selectively sharing information across tasks based on the overlap in sparsity patterns, which suggests a focus on optimization and regularization techniques (cs.AI). The experiments involve image classification and natural language processing tasks, indicating a potential fit with computer vision (cs.CV) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper mentions the use of low-dimensional subspaces, which is a common technique in signal processing (cs.SI).
